This paper focuses on group decision making and social influence within groups, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of a recommender system, which falls under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the organization of social events, which could be considered a topic in the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY) or Sound (cs.SD). Finally, the paper proposes a decision cascading model, which could be related to the sub-category of Graphics (cs.GR) in terms of visualizing the decision-making process.
